  "prompt": "What are some lesser-known sights to see when visiting Icheon, South Korea?",
  "response": "When visiting Icheon, South Korea, you might want to check out some lesser-known sights that offer unique experiences beyond the more popular destinations. Here are a few suggestions:\n\n1. **Icheon Ceramics Village**: While Icheon is known for its ceramics, make sure to explore the small studios and workshops where local artisans create beautiful pottery. You can even try your hand at making your own ceramic piece.\n\n2. **Icheon Termeden**: This German-style spa resort offers relaxing baths and saunas in a natural setting. It's a great place to unwind and experience Korean spa culture.\n\n3. **Seolbong Park**: This peaceful park features a beautiful lake, walking trails, and seasonal flower displays. It's an ideal spot for a leisurely stroll or a picnic.\n\n4. **Icheon Rice Culture Complex**: Learn about the history and cultural significance of rice in Korea at this interesting complex. You can see traditional rice planting techniques, explore exhibitions, and even taste dishes made with Icheon rice.\n\n5. **Haegang Ceramics Museum**: A museum dedicated to Korean ceramics, Haegang Ceramics Museum showcases both traditional and contemporary works. It's a great place to appreciate the artistry and craftsmanship of Korean pottery.\n\n6. **Silmido Island**: For those interested in history, a visit to this island, which has a dramatic past and has featured in Korean movies, can be intriguing. Although it requires a bit of travel, the historical context makes it worthwhile.\n\n7. **Sangwonsa Temple**: Located in the surrounding area of Icheon, Sangwonsa Temple is a serene spot that offers a glimpse into Buddhist practices and architecture in Korea.\n\nExploring these lesser-known sights will give you a deeper appreciation of Icheon's rich cultural heritage and natural beauty.",
